On 29 May, farmers from Aragatsavan closed the highway and railway and protested against the rising of the price of irrigation water. [size=no report]

On March 2nd, unknown gunmen riding camels and horses abducted four pastoralists at a well in Katur (North Darfur), following an attack by the same group earlier in the day at Dobo Umda. They proceeded to steal 310 sheep and goats.

A nationwide protest took place on January 11th, in the main cities of Colombia to demand the resignation of the Attorney General of Colombia Nestor Humberto Martinez. Martinez has been accused of corruption. The protests were in several cities including Armenia in Quindio.

On 07 November 2019, in Ovalle, Coquimbo region, people demonstrated over general discontent with the government. Police Forces of Chile clashed against a group of rioters when barricades were built. The group's demands include reforms in education, healthcare and pension policies, among other things. Two rioters were arreted. A total of 3,000 demonstrated in Coquimbo, La Serena and Ovalle. [size=3,000 total]
On April 06, 2019, clashes took place between regime forces and opposition rebels in Al-Rashdeen area west of Aleppo city. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.
On October 18, hundreds of protesters from the movement against the political system in Lebanon gathered in Ghazir. [size=hundreds]
17 June. Akyode and Chala Ethnic Militias clashed in Keri over a ritual of welcoming the cultivation of yam. Three people were injured.

On May 13, members of the All Assam Students' Union (AASU) staged a protest in front of the Subdivisional Office in Sarupathar city (Golaghat, Assam), against wrong inclusion of the names of the people in draft National Register of Citizens (NRC) list. [size=no report]

As reported on 9 December 2019, in Lujan (San Luis), a group of women protested against a case of abuse and performed a new version of "A rapist in your path" (performance from women's groups against gender-based violence). They marched from Plaza Belgrano towards the D.A. Office, the police station and the City Hall. [size=no report]

On March 24, 2019, in Cruzeiro, Sao Paulo, a man was shot to death by armed men. The victim had drug trafficking charges against him. There is no report on the identity of the perpetrators or crime motivation. 1 fatality.

On 25 May 2019, an IED planted by unidentified gunmen exploded at the Al-Jazarah Junction near the Red Crescent building in the city of Ar-Raqqa, causing material damage. Neither injuries nor fatalities were reported.

On 27 January 2019, near the RR-205 road, connecting Boa Vista and Alto Alegre (Roraima), the body of a woman was found with a gunshot to the back of her head. Neither the identity of the perpetrator nor the reasons behind the crime are known. No arrests were reported.

properties.actor2: Police Forces of Yemen (2012-) Special Security Forces
properties.notes: On August 21, Islahi gunmen manning a checkpoint in Al-Birayn area in Taizz governorate, southwestern Yemen, reportedly attempted to kill Special Security forces commander Jamil Aqlan as his convoy arrived at the checkpoint, with no report of fatalities nor injuries. According to the source, the gunmen were planning to blame the killing on the Support and Reinforcement Brigade in order to then accuse them of breaching the truce agreement led by local mediation in the area.

On November 10, 2019, in Joao Pessoa, Paraiba, a man was shot to death by armed men on a motorcycle in Cristo. According to reports, a dispute between rival criminal factions was the crime motivation.

properties.assoc_actor_1: CV: Red Command; GDE: Guardians of the State
properties.notes: On January 25, 2019, in Fortaleza, Ceara, a group set a van on fire in Dias Macedo and two tractors in Planalto. One bus was set on fire in Sao Bento and a second one in Jardim Jatoba by five menas, all as a response to the enforcement of stricter rules in Ceara prisons. According to ongoing investigations, criminal factions operating in Ceara - PCC, CV and GDE - would have joined forces to retaliate the statements on prisoners' division made by the new state penitentiary secretary.

On 21 January, AAP members staged a protest in Abohar (Fazilka, Punjab) after a man was killed after his motorcycle was hit by a stray bull near Amarpura village. This protest is associated with the AAP's ongoing dharna at Nehru Park in the city against the stray cattle issue.

On January 24 2019,in Guatemala City, people protested against the amnesty law 5377. The law seeks to grant an amnesty to persons accused of serious crimes committed during the armed conflict. [size=no report]

properties.assoc_actor_1: Police Forces of Ivory Coast (2011-) Prison Guards
properties.notes: On 31 December 2019, the police forces clashed with the prison guards in Man town (Tonkpi, Montagnes). The clash broke out after a prison guard out of duty, resisted a police control. His colleagues alerted, reportedly joined him later to confront with the police forces. No fatality and/or casualty reported. [size=no report]

On 30 Jan, police blocked a protest march by scholars and students in Jammu city (J&K), from Jammu University to the Civil Secretariat. The march was held against a recent decision by the State Administration Council regarding the conversion of various posts of teachers in the Education Department.

properties.assoc_actor_1: Students (India); AJYCP: Asom Jatiyatabadi Yuva Chatra Parishad; Teachers (India); Labour Group (India); Adivasi Ethnic Group (India)
properties.notes: As reported on 15 December, members of AASU, AJYCP and 30 other organisations of indigenous people, senior citizens, students, artists, singers, intellectuals and teachers among others held protests in Dibrugarh district (Assam) agitating against the Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 2019 (CAA). [size=no report]

properties.actor2: Police Forces of Mexico (2018-) State Police
properties.notes: On 26 September 2019, in San Pablo Xochimehuacan, Puebla, Puebla, six armed men clashed with state police officers. One man died and another one was injured.
25 February. Unidentified warplanes struck AS hide out at Shabeeley village.
From September 10 to October 9, in Mohandiseen, journalists at Tahrir Newspaper staged a sit-in protesting against a planned reduction in wages [size=no report].

properties.actor1: Military Forces of Yemen (2016-) Supreme Political Council
properties.notes: A young shepherd boy was seriously wounded by a Houthi-planted landmine in Rama area of Maris, Ad Dali governorate.

properties.assoc_actor_1: APHC-AJK: All Parties Hurriyat Conference-Azad Jammu and Kashmir; Lawyers (Pakistan); Students (Pakistan)
properties.notes: On November 17, Hurriyat organizations along with lawyers, members of civil society and students held a protest outside National Press Club in Islamabad city (Islamabad, Federal Capital Territory) to condemn the Indian government's continued imposition of lockdown and communication blockade in Indian Administered Kashmir and to demand intervention from the United Nations and the international community in support of right to self-determination of people of Kashmir. [size=no report]
12 March. Suspected AS militants shot and killed an unidentified youth, suspected to be a government soldier in Hodan District.

Arrests: As reported between October 28-31, total 85 Syrian migrants who entered Turkey illegally were detained by the operations of the border patrol units of the Turkish Army and Gendarmerie forces in Altinozu and Kirikhan districts of Hatay.

On 17 November 2019, suspected Taliban fighters planted a rickshaw bomb in a bazaar in Tagab district, Kapisa province which wounded 7 civilians and an Afghan police officers. No fatalities were reported.
On March 1, employees of different departments blocked the National Highway and staged a protest in Thatta town (Thatta, Sindh), against NBP authorities demanding their salaries. [size=large]

properties.actor1: Military Forces of Libya (2014-) Haftar Faction
properties.actor2: Military Forces of Libya (2016-) Government of National Accord
properties.notes: On 21 December 2019, LNA and GNA forces clashed at the Hamza Camp and Khallatat Street near Mashru Al Hadba, no casualties reported.
On 05-February-2019, 3 Afghan Policemen were killed by Taiban militants in the Haidarabad area of Nahri Saraj district, Helmand province.
On 05-April-2019, 1 Afghan soldier was killed by Taliban militants in the Sirkanay district of Kunar province.

properties.admin1: Bangsamoro Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao
properties.notes: Seven people were killed during an attack by one clan on another in Barangay Sangbay, Hadji Muhtamad, Basilan province on January 3, 2019. Five others were wounded.
On 06 May 2019, transport workers blocked the Cuautla-Amecameca Road at the level of Atlatlahucan to protest against Moto taxi and other transport regulations. [size=no report]
On 31 March, 2019, regime ground forces fired rockets at the town of Tahtaya with neither injuries nor fatalities reported.

On 16 Dec 2019, in Casimiro de Abreu, Rio de Janeiro, residents of the Professor Souza district demonstrated over the closure of a detour on the BR-101 highway. The group set tires on fire and blocked the highway. [size=no report]

properties.actor1: Military Forces of Yemen (2016-) Supreme Political Council
properties.notes: On 21 March, pro-Houthi forces reportedly fired mortar shells and heavy weapons at anti-Houthi groups east of As Salih city of Al Hali district, northeast of Al Hudaydah city, western Yemen. No fatalities nor injuries reported.

properties.actor2: Police Forces of India (2014-) Home Guards
properties.notes: On 24 June (assumed), a Home Guard personnel was hit and dragged 300 metres by the car of a BJP leader in Rewari city (Haryana) after he asked them to follow the traffic rules. No injuries were reported. [size=no report]

On Jan. 14, 2019: Entrepreneurs and their employees protested in front of th EVN building in Plovdiv against the planned increase of 37% in electricity prices for businesses, saying it would lead to losing jobs and very high costs.

On 20 January, members of National Corps and other activists protested in Cherkasy against the Odessa city mayor, construction in coastal and historic areas in Odessa and attacks on activists. [size=no report]
On July 06 2019, 2 Taliban, including a commander, were killed during a raid by Afghan forces in Dashti Qala district, Takhar.

properties.actor1: Unidentified Armed Group (Democratic Republic of Congo)
properties.notes: 10 April 2019 (on or before). An unidentified armed group abducted Concern NGO employees in Kitwiguru, Rutshuru (no coordinates available). The abductees were released after a ransom of $5,000, three computers and two phones was paid.

properties.source: OSCE SMM-Ukraine; DPR Armed Forces Press Service
properties.notes: On 26 December, the Ukrainian Forces fired IFVs, grenade launchers, heavy machine guns and small arms at the positions of the Donbass People's Militia in the area of Staromykhaylivka, Donetsk. The OSCE SMM observed a total of 1 explosions involving unknown weapons near Staromykhaylivka.

Property destruction: As reported on September 28 2019, Lebanese military and Police forces demolished buildings that were constructed by Syrians on the land of the El Qaa municipality with smuggled construction materials from Syria.

On 27 June, 2019, QSD carried out a security operation in Abu Hamam in southern Deir-ez-Zor countryside against suspected IS sleeper cells. During the raids in Abu Hamam and Gharanij, 10 suspected IS members were arrested.

properties.assoc_actor_1: PML-N: Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz; Government of Pakistan (2018-)
properties.notes: On December 8, large number of PML-N MNAs, MPAs and workers held a protest in Chiniot city (Chiniot, Punjab) against the PTI government's economic policies alleging it of creating inflation, and hike in electricity and gas tariffs. [size=large]
On May 15 2019, students and professors from several universities in Taua in Ceara protested against the budgetary cuts announced by the national government. [size=no report]

properties.source: Radio Television Nationale du Burundi; Undisclosed Source
properties.notes: 08 June. Protesters demonstrate against French media coverage of events in Burundi in Bubanza city of Bubanza province during nationwide demonstrations. [size=no report]

properties.source: Ministry of Defence of Ukraine; JFO HQ press centre
properties.notes: On 31 July, the NAF rebel forces fired heavy machine guns and IFVs at the governmental positions near Bohdanivka, Donetsk.
In July citizens and workers of Lujan, Buenos Aires, protested against the bad conditions of the health center in the district. The group demands improvements in hospital facilities. [size=no report]
